    "24759299": {
      "title": "Packing analogue of k-radius sequences",
      "abstract": "Let k be a positive integer. A sequence s 1 , s 2 , \u017a , s m over an n -element A alphabet is a packing k -radius sequence, if for all pairs of indices ( i , j ) , such that 1 \u017a i < j \u017a m and j - i \u017a k , the sets { s i , s j } are pairwise different 2 -element subsets of A . Let g k ( n ) denote the length of a longest k -radius sequence over A . We give a construction demonstrating that for every k = \u017a c n \u03b1 \u017a , where c and \u03b1 are fixed reals such that c 0 and 0 \u017a \u03b1 < 1 2 , g k ( n ) = n 2 2 k ( 1 - o ( 1 ) ) . For a constant k we show that g k ( n ) = n 2 2 k - O ( n 1.525 ) . Moreover, we prove an upper bound for g k ( n ) that allows us to show that g k ( n ) = n ( 1 + o ( 1 ) ) for every k = \u017a c n \u03b1 \u017a , where c 0 and 1 2 < \u03b1 < 1 ."
    }
  }
}